# ── Build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Rust (agent/)
agent/target/
**/*.rs.bk
# Go (control/) — compiled binaries and test/coverage output
control/control
control/**/*.test
cli/cli
*.out
coverage.out
# Swift (macapp/) build products
macapp/.build/
# Assembled .app bundle from macapp/assemble-app.sh (build output; rebuilt on demand)
build/
# Python (sdk/) caches
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
sdk/python/build/
sdk/python/dist/
sdk/python/*.egg-info/

# ── Local run artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# scripts/prove-local.sh writes its throwaway Postgres/MinIO data, logs, and the
# proof ledger under .artifacts/. Logs and pidfiles from any ad-hoc local runs.
# Never commit these.
.artifacts/
scripts/*.log
*.log
*.pid

# ── Secrets / local config ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
.secrets/
# The agent's runtime config holds a worker token — commit agent.example.toml,
# never the real one.
agent/agent.toml

# ── Editor / OS cruft ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~

# ── Design sources ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The layered logo master (logo/cx_logo.psd, ~8 MB) is the editable brand source,
# kept local to keep clones lean. The flat source PNG + the flat masters
# (cx-mark-white, cx-app-icon) ARE committed; scripts/cx_trace.py + cx_logo.py
# regenerate the metal render from the PNG. The full-res 1080px render master stays
# local (logo/cx-metal*); the right-sized served copies live in web/assets and ARE
# committed.
*.psd
logo/cx-metal*

# ── PROTECTED ASSETS (SACRED — see BLACKHOLE.md) ─────────────────────────────
# Models, weights, datasets, and caches are expensive or impossible to
# regenerate. They are gitignored so they are NEVER committed, but they must
# NEVER be deleted or moved either: a user who pulled a model yesterday still
# has it working today. The collapse restructures the code that loads them, not
# the artifacts. Do not `git clean` these away.
models/
data/
*.gguf
*.safetensors
*.mlx
*.bin

# ── Render pixel artifacts (regenerable — kept local, never committed) ────────
# Every rendered PNG/JPG, cached .blend geometry, and calibration frame is
# regenerated by render/build_*.py from the committed builders + specs. The
# pixels bloated the repo to ~800 MB (a 105 MB foam cache even exceeded GitHub's
# 100 MB file limit), so ALL render images/binaries are stripped from history and
# ignored here. The TRAIL stays committed: the .py builders, the .md reports +
# specs, the reference .pdf datasheets. Re-run a builder to regenerate any image.
render/**/*.png
render/**/*.jpg
render/**/*.jpeg
render/**/*.webp
render/**/*.exr
render/**/*.blend
render/**/*.blend1
render/**/*.glb
render/cache/

# agent worktrees / local tooling
.claude/
web/admin-demo.html

# rust crate build dirs (spec-engine, token-spec-poc, renderer)
target/

# python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# regenerable render diagnostics (pixel artifacts; the builders + ledgers are the trail)
diag_images/

# raw bulk tuning trace (69MB machine log; the distilled reports + smaller ledgers are the trail)
docs/speed-lane-reports/spec-lab/tuning_ledger.jsonl

# pytest's discovery cache is generated at every repository depth. The claim and
# source-fingerprint scanners must never mistake it for a product document.
**/.pytest_cache/
